summary: Some Conserns I Have About ‘Vape Nation’
body:
Some Conserns I Have About ‘Vape Nation’

I’m going to start with a sort of disclaimer, I’m not anybody’s doctor, parent, or [insert authority figure here] and if you wanna vape or whatever that’s your business, but I would like to air one concern on the matter.

People think it’s a safe alternative to smoking, and I would argue an addiction or dependency to anything (especially a drug such a nicotine) isn’t healthy period. It’s not just that though.

Let me tell you about a little something called Popcorn Lung.

Via Wikipedia: Bronchiolitis Obliterans, also known as Popcorn Lung and Constrictive Bronchiolitis , is a disease that results in obstruction of the smallest airways of the lungs (bronchioles) due to inflammation. Symptoms include dry cough, shortness of breath, wheezing, and feeling tired.

This disease has a variety of causes, but the ones I’m focusing on today are; Exposure to toxic fumes, certain orally administered emergency medicines, and lastly and most significantly industrial inhalants.

Specifically referencing a factory that manufactured a specific diacetyl butter-like popcorn flavoring, which is no coincidence to how this disease got it’s nick-name.

Inhaling anything that isn’t air is a risk factor for damaging your lungs to be frank, but breathing flavor laced nicotine?! It’s orders of magnitude worse.

‘But Anna’, I hear you say, ‘surely they wouldn’t sell it if it was bad for—’ they used to put cocaine in soda and sell it to people, they used to advertise Heroine as a non-addictive alternative to morphine, the tobacco industry had and has gotten away with a lot of boondoggles.

What I’m saying is in a few years or so (certainly more time than they should get away with selling vapes) there’s going to be a whistleblower or a study of the long term effects that comes out and you’re going to hear the term Popcorn Lung again in reference to the fallout.

I’m just fed up with corporations not taking the public health seriously if it makes them a quick buck in the short term, because even if they get caught the fines are just a slap on the wrist….

summary: I know it looks a little gross but I swear this is the best way I’ve ever found to drink a protein shake. I mix 1/2 cup coconut...
body: I know it looks a little gross but I swear this is the best way I’ve ever found to drink a protein shake. I mix ½ cup coconut milk, 1 scoop chocolate whey isolate protein powder, 2 tbsp hemp protein powder, and coffee then top it off with ice. It tastes exactly like an iced mocha from Starbucks but it packs in 43g of protein and 6g of fiber for 300 calories.
